eUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/codemeta.json"}, {"result": {"value": "Daniel Garijo", "type": "Agent", "email": "daniel.garijo@upm.es", "affiliation": "Ontology Engineering Group at the Artificial Intelligence Department of the Computer Science Faculty of Universidad Polit\u00e9cnica de Madrid", "identifier": "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0454-7145"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/codemeta.json"}], "has_build_file": [{"result": {"value": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/pyproject.toml", "type": "Url", "format": "pyproject.toml"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "file_exploration", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/pyproject.toml"}], "has_package_file": [{"result": {"value": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/pyproject.toml", "type": "Url"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "code_parser", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/pyproject.toml"}], "continuous_integration": [{"result": {"value": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/.github/workflows/rsmetacheck.yml", "type": "Url"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "file_exploration"}], "installation": [{"result": {"value": "This project uses [Poetry](https://python-poetry.org/) for dependency management and requires Python 3.10\n\n1. Clone this repository:\n\n   ```bash\n   git clone https://github.com/Anas-Elhounsri/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify.git\n   cd Metadata-Adoption-Quantify\n   ```\n\n2. Install the package and its dependencies:\n\n   ```bash\n   poetry install\n   ```\n\n3. Set up SoMEF where you will be prompted to enter your GitHub authentication token optionally if you wish to have more rate limit per hour. More information can be found [here](https://github.com/KnowledgeCaptureAndDiscovery/somef)\n\n   ```bash\n   somef configure\n   ```\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Installation", "parent_header": ["Metadata-Adoption-Quantify"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/README.md"}], "usage": [{"result": {"value": "The tool is accessible via the `quantify` command. All commands should be prefixed with `poetry run` if you are not in the poetry shell.\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Usage", "parent_header": ["Metadata-Adoption-Quantify"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/README.md"}, {"result": {"value": "Calculates the final percentages and insights for each RQ.\n\n```bash\npoetry run quantify calculate --input repos.json --rq-results-dir rq_results --results-dir final_results --cluster default\n```\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "3. Calculate Final Results", "parent_header": ["Metadata-Adoption-Quantify", "Usage", "Available Commands"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/README.md"}, {"result": {"value": "You can still access help for any command by running:\n\n```bash\npoetry run quantify --help\n```\n\nAfter running the `calculate` command for a cluster, you get the final summary:\n\n```bash\n{\n    \"escape\": {\n        \"cff\": 5.88235294117647,\n        \"readme\": 100.0,\n        \"package\": 41.17647058823529,\n        \"authors\": 11.76470588235294,\n        \"contributors\": 17.647058823529413,\n        \"license\": 100.0,\n        \"codemeta\": 88.23529411764706,\n        \"zenodo\": 29.411764705882355,\n        \"zenodo_doi\": 41.17647058823529,\n        \"none\": 0.0\n    }\n}\n```\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "Main Menu (Alternative)", "parent_header": ["Metadata-Adoption-Quantify", "Usage"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/README.md"}], "run": [{"result": {"value": "Extracts metadata from a list of GitHub repositories provided in a JSON file.\n\n```bash\npoetry run quantify somef --input repos.json --output-dir somef_outputs --threshold 0.8\n```\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "1. Run SoMEF on Repositories", "parent_header": ["Metadata-Adoption-Quantify", "Usage", "Available Commands"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/README.md"}, {"result": {"value": "Analyzes SoMEF outputs to answer specific research questions.\n\n```bash\npoetry run quantify rqs --somef-dir somef_outputs --input-repos repos.json --output-dir rq_results --cluster default\n```\n\n_Note: `--input-repos` is required for RQ2 analysis._\n\nThe input (in the case of the example that would be `repos.json`) should be a JSON file with the following format:\n\n```json\n[\n  {\n    \"github_url\": \"https://github.com/foo/bar\"\n  },\n  {\n    \"github_url\": \"https://github.com/dgarijo/Widoco/\"\n  }\n]\n```\n", "type": "Text_excerpt", "original_header": "2. Run RQ Analysis", "parent_header": ["Metadata-Adoption-Quantify", "Usage", "Available Commands"]}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "header_analysis", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/README.md"}], "full_title": [{"result": {"type": "String", "value": "Metadata-Adoption-Quantify"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "regular_expression", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/README.md"}], "logo": [{"result": {"type": "Url", "value": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/logo.png"}, "confidence": 1, "technique": "regular_expression", "source": "https://raw.githubusercontent.com/SoftwareUnderstanding/Metadata-Adoption-Quantify/main/README.md"}]}